South African Nominal House Prices Slipped 0.7% in March, Absa Group Says

-- B y   A g n e s   N i k o i
-- 
2011-04-07T06:00:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/south-african-nominal-house-prices-fell-0-7-in-march-absa-group-says.html
The average nominal value of a
medium-sized house in  South Africa  decreased an annual 0.7% in
March,  Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  said in an e-mailed statement today.
House prices are set to fall by over 3 percent in real terms
this year, the bank said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at 
 anikoi@bloomberg.net  